# Formatting Standards

## Prettier Configuration

### Base Configuration

```javascript
// .prettierrc.js
module.exports = {
  semi: true,
  trailingComma: 'all',
  singleQuote: true,
  printWidth: 80,
  tabWidth: 2,
  useTabs: false,
  bracketSpacing: true,
  jsxBracketSameLine: false,
  arrowParens: 'always',
  endOfLine: 'lf',
};
```

### File-Specific Overrides

```javascript
// .prettierrc.js overrides
module.exports = {
  overrides: [
    {
      files: '*.{md,mdc}',
      options: {
        parser: 'markdown',
        proseWrap: 'always',
        printWidth: 80,
        tabWidth: 2,
        endOfLine: 'lf',
      },
    },
    {
      files: '*.{ts,tsx}',
      options: {
        parser: 'typescript',
        semi: true,
        trailingComma: 'all',
        endOfLine: 'lf',
      },
    },
  ],
};
```

## Markdown Lint Rules

### File Structure

```markdown
---
description: 'Use single quotes for strings'
globs: 'pattern'
---

# Title (H1)

## Section (H2)

### Subsection (H3)

Content with proper spacing.
```

### Rule Configuration

````javascript
// .markdownlint.json
{
  "default": true,
  "MD001": true,           // Heading levels should only increment by one level
  "MD002": true,           // First heading should be a top-level heading
  "MD003": {              // Heading style
    "style": "atx"        // Use # style headings
  },
  "MD004": {              // Unordered list style
    "style": "dash"       // Use - for unordered lists
  },
  "MD005": true,          // Consistent list indentation
  "MD006": true,          // Consider starting lists at beginning of line
  "MD007": {              // Unordered list indentation
    "indent": 2           // Use 2 spaces for indentation
  },
  "MD009": {              // No trailing spaces
    "br_spaces": 2,       // Allow 2 spaces for line break
    "list_item_empty_lines": false
  },
  "MD010": {              // No hard tabs
    "code_blocks": false  // Allow tabs in code blocks
  },
  "MD011": true,          // Reversed link syntax
  "MD012": {              // Multiple consecutive blank lines
    "maximum": 1          // Allow at most 1 blank line
  },
  "MD013": {              // Line length
    "line_length": 80,    // Max line length
    "code_blocks": false, // Don't check code blocks
    "tables": false       // Don't check tables
  },
  "MD014": true,          // Dollar signs used before commands
  "MD018": true,          // Space after hash on atx style heading
  "MD019": true,          // No multiple spaces after hash on atx style heading
  "MD020": true,          // No space inside hashes on closed atx style heading
  "MD021": true,          // No multiple spaces inside hashes on closed atx style
  "MD022": true,          // Headings should be surrounded by blank lines
  "MD023": true,          // Headings must start at beginning of line
  "MD024": {              // Multiple headings with same content
    "allow_different_nesting": true
  },
  "MD025": true,          // Single title/h1 tag
  "MD026": true,          // Trailing punctuation in heading
  "MD027": true,          // Multiple spaces after blockquote symbol
  "MD028": true,          // Blank line inside blockquote
  "MD029": {              // Ordered list item prefix
    "style": "one"        // Use 1. for all items
  },
  "MD030": true,          // Spaces after list markers
  "MD031": true,          // Fenced code blocks should be surrounded by blank lines
  "MD032": true,          // Lists should be surrounded by blank lines
  "MD033": {              // Inline HTML
    "allowed_elements": ["br", "img"]
  },
  "MD034": true,          // Bare URL used
  "MD035": {              // Horizontal rule style
    "style": "---"        // Use --- for horizontal rules
  },
  "MD036": true,          // Emphasis used instead of heading
  "MD037": true,          // Spaces inside emphasis markers
  "MD038": true,          // Spaces inside code span elements
  "MD039": true,          // Spaces inside link text
  "MD040": true,          // Fenced code blocks should have a language specified
  "MD041": true,          // First line in file should be a top-level heading
  "MD042": true,          // No empty links
  "MD043": false,         // Required heading structure
  "MD044": false,         // Proper names should have proper capitalization
  "MD045": true,          // Images should have alternate text
  "MD046": {              // Code block style
    "style": "fenced"     // Use ``` for code blocks
  },
  "MD047": true,          // Files should end with a single newline character
  "MD048": {              // Code fence style
    "style": "backtick"   // Use ``` for code fences
  }
}
````

## Best Practices

### 1. File Organization

- One topic per file
- Clear file naming
- Proper frontmatter
- Consistent structure
- Logical sections

### 2. Content Formatting

- Proper heading hierarchy
- Consistent list formatting
- Code block language specification
- Proper link formatting
- Clean spacing

### 3. Code Examples

- Language specification
- Proper indentation
- Clear comments
- Meaningful examples
- Consistent style

### 4. Documentation

- Clear descriptions
- Proper quotes
- Valid globs
- Related patterns
- Version control

